write relates to one in terms of a "limit" relation which limits the size of its result set to 1
relates to 1 generates a #{relation_name}_relation method that gives direct access to its limit relation object
has many, et al
attributes can't have the same name as class methods on Tuple or they shadow them... how can this be circumvented?
  either disallow attributes with those names
  alias the existing methods to something else (could break other code)
  change the api